<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 3:21PM CDT  by NWS Huntsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Jackson and
southeastern Franklin Counties through 400 PM CDT...
At 321 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Skyline, or 18 miles north of Scottsboro, moving
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Scottsboro, Bridgeport, Stevenson, Cowan, Hollywood, Skyline,
Section, Pisgah, Sewanee and Anderson.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
